#Text=Pakistan International
#Text=Airlines sacrifices goat , resumes ATR flights
#Text=Wednesday , December 21 , 2016
#Text=Images of Pakistan International Airlines sacrificing a goat went viral on Monday as the beleaguered state-run airline resumed ATR flights .
#Text=All ten ATRs in its fleet were grounded last week in the aftermath of a crash near Havelian earlier this month .
#Text=PIA ground staff ritually slaughtered the black goat beside an ATR-42 , the same type of aircraft lost in the disaster .
#Text=The move is thought to ward off bad luck in Pakistan .
#Text=The ATR-42 was the company 's first ATR back in service following the crash .
#Text=PIA said on December 15 they had chartered a Lockheed C-130 Hercules from the air force to resume cancelled services .
#Text=The crashed aircraft , from file .
#Text=Image : Asuspine .
#Text=PIA Flight 661 , an ATR-42 just under ten years old , crashed into mountainous terrain in the Abbottabad region of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa two weeks ago .
#Text=The crash killed all 47 on board and left burning wreckage strewn for several kilometres .
#Text=PIA still operate five ATR-42s and five ATR-72 s.
#Text=The Civil Aviation Authority ( CAA ) announced inspections on December 11 .
#Text=The airline expected disruption to flights to smaller airports .
#Text=Flight 661 was heading to Islamabad , having taken off from Chitral on a domestic flight .
#Text=The plane reported engine trouble and lost control before the crash .
#Text=PIA sacrificed the goat at Islamabad 's Benazir Bhutto International Airport , ahead of a successful test flight to Multan .
#Text=PIA stated ground staff acted on their own volition and were not influenced by managers .
#Text=Another PIA ATR experienced troubles ahead of takeoff on December 11 and aborted the flight .
#Text=The airline denied local media claims an engine caught fire .
#Text=Pakistani media has claimed Flight 661 was operating with some known technical faults .
#Text=The Aviation Herald reports receiving information to the contrary , and the airline also denies this .
#Text=The CAA has left decisions on returning aircraft to service at the discretion of PIA and ATR .
#Text=A CAA letter to PIA expressed concern over engine failures at the airline , and accused PIA of " shortcomings in maintenance [ and ] quality assurance .
